byline.contributor: Falih Hassan and Omar al-Jawoshy contributed reporting

abstract: Islamic State claims responsibility for suicide attack that killed two Iraqi generals in Anbar Province; attackers used American-made Humvees stolen from Iraqi army to sneak into close range of Iraqi convoys and detonate explosives onboard vehicle.
lead_paragraph: Two explosives-rigged American-made Humvees blew up near the generals’ convoy, dealing another setback to the faltering campaign to retake Anbar Province.

headline.main: ISIS Suicide Attack Kills 2 Iraqi Generals Near Ramadi
